---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Autumn — Fall Terms That Score Big"
  description="Autumn and fall words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. EQUINOX (23pts), HARVEST (13pts), PUMPKIN (17pts). Seasonal vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble autumn words, equinox scrabble points, harvest scrabble, pumpkin scrabble, fall terms scrabble, seasonal words scrabble, autumn vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Autumn — Fall Terms That Score Big","description":"Autumn and fall words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. EQUINOX (23pts), HARVEST (13pts), PUMPKIN (17pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-autumn"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is EQUINOX a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! EQUINOX scores 23 points (E=1, Q=10, U=1, I=1, N=1, O=1, X=8) in Scrabble. It uses both Q and X tiles for massive value. It refers to the day when day and night are equal length. Valid in SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play HARVEST in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. HARVEST scores 13 points (H=4, A=1, R=1, V=4, E=1, S=1, T=1) as a 7-letter bingo candidate. The H=4 and V=4 together provide 8 points, making it worth 63 points with the bingo bonus."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PUMPKIN valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PUMPKIN scores 17 points (P=3, U=1, M=3, P=3, K=5, I=1, N=1) as a 7-letter word. Double P=3 and K=5 make this autumn staple a bingo candidate worth 67 points total."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Autumn — Fall Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Autumn brings more than falling leaves — it delivers a harvest of high-scoring Scrabble words. From astronomical events to seasonal produce, fall vocabulary is rich with Q tiles, X tiles, K tiles, and V tiles that can turn your rack golden.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">23 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">EQUINOX</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PUMPKIN</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">HARVEST</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SQUASH</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Autumn Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">EQUINOX — 23 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">E=1, Q=10, U=1, I=1, N=1, O=1, X=8 · 7 letters · Q + X powerhouse</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The moment when day and night are equal length. EQUINOX is extraordinary — it uses BOTH Q=10 and X=8 in a single 7-letter word for 23 base points. With the bingo bonus, that's 73 points. One of the highest-scoring natural bingos in the dictionary.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎃 PUMPKIN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 pts · P=3, U=1, M=3, P=3, K=5, I=1, N=1 · Bingo candidate</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌾 HARVEST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · H=4, A=1, R=1, V=4, E=1, S=1, T=1 · Bingo candidate</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍂 FOLIAGE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · F=4, O=1, L=1, I=1, A=1, G=2, E=1 · Autumn leaves</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌰 CHESTNUT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · C=3, H=4, E=1, S=1, T=1, N=1, U=1, T=1 · Autumn nut</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Seasonal Vocabulary</h2>
      <p>Autumn's rich vocabulary provides consistent scoring from seasonal themes:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SQUASH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CRISP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BONFIRE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CIDER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MAPLE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Autumn Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">EQUINOX is the dream bingo:</span> Using Q=10 AND X=8 in one word (23pts + 50 bonus = 73pts) is rare and devastating. If you hold Q, U, and X simultaneously, this is your golden play.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PUMPKIN uses double P and K:</span> P=3 appears twice plus K=5 for 17 points from 7 tiles. As a bingo (67pts), PUMPKIN is surprisingly powerful for such a common word.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">HARVEST pairs H and V:</span> H=4 and V=4 together give 8 points from just two tiles. HARVEST (13pts) is easy to spot and plays well as a 7-letter bingo (63pts).</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Autumn words are <span class="text-white font-medium">bingo specialists</span>. EQUINOX (Q+X), HARVEST (H+V), and PUMPKIN (PP+K) are all exactly 7 letters, making them natural bingo plays. When building towards a bingo with high-value tiles, think autumn — three of the best bingo candidates live in this vocabulary.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-halloween-scary/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Halloween Scary</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-summer/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Summer</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-winter/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Winter</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-tropical/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Tropical</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-seasonal-winter-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Winter Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-halloween/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Halloween</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-nature-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Nature Words</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid autumn word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
